00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:57,680
And also...

560
00:27:58,359 --> 00:27:59,160
I...

561
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:01,240
I shouldn't place all my happiness...

562
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,519
...on you and our son.

563
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:08,240
My happiness should come from myself.

564
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:11,200
No, there's a bit of a problem with that, you know?

565
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:14,119
You should place your happiness...

566
00:28:14,119 --> 00:28:15,559
...on us.

567
00:28:15,799 --> 00:28:17,680
And I, I should also place my happiness...

568
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:19,119
...on you.

569
00:28:19,119 --> 00:28:20,279
But neither of us should...

570
00:28:20,279 --> 00:28:21,240
...place our happiness...

571
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:23,119
...on that little jerk.

572
00:28:24,359 --> 00:28:26,839
He's about to take the college entrance exam, right?

573
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:29,119
He'll say "off to college" and be gone.

574
00:28:29,680 --> 00:28:31,039
He'll leave us in the dust then.

575
00:28:31,559 --> 00:28:33,680
He'll have his own life, right?

576
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:36,440
We should just ignore him.

577
00:28:37,039 --> 00:28:38,559
We'll be happy on our own.

578
00:28:38,559 --> 00:28:39,920
Let me tell you, starting today...

579
00:28:40,079 --> 00:28:42,680
I... I looked up a famous quote, you know?

580
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:44,200
I think it's absolutely right.

581
00:28:44,759 --> 00:28:47,279
It's about how a wife...

582
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:49,799
...I should treat like a lover.

583
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:51,880
Wang Chunsheng, let me tell you...

584
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,480
That Xiao Zhang from your department store...

585
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:54,799
And that whole string of things before...

586
00:28:54,799 --> 00:28:56,559
You still haven't explained them clearly to me.

587
00:28:56,559 --> 00:28:57,799
Look, look, look.

588
00:28:58,599 --> 00:28:59,759
I bought you this.

589
00:29:00,039 --> 00:29:01,039
This... this...

590
00:29:01,119 --> 00:29:02,599
You always said not to buy you things.

591
00:29:02,599 --> 00:29:04,480
But they say...

592
00:29:04,799 --> 00:29:06,599
...even if you just buy some meat or something...

593
00:29:08,240 --> 00:29:08,920
Take a look.

594
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:11,240
Stop shaking it around.

595
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:13,880
Aren't you just wasting money again?

596
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:14,680
No, you... I think...

597
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:15,920
How much did this cost?

598
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:16,559
As a woman...

599
00:29:16,559 --> 00:29:19,039
I believe you deserve to have this in your life.

600
00:29:19,119 --> 00:29:20,680
Come on, come on, let me put it on you.

601
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:21,759
No, this...

602
00:29:22,640 --> 00:29:25,000
Don't throw this box away later.

603
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,880
Look at the ring, not the box.

604
00:29:26,880 --> 00:29:27,279
No, no.

605
00:29:27,279 --> 00:29:29,920
Don't throw the box away, I'll use it for something else later.

606
00:29:29,920 --> 00:29:31,119
This is really nice.

607
00:29:31,119 --> 00:29:32,240
Yeah, it can even be a night light.

608
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:33,160
When you get up to use the bathroom or something.

609
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:34,039
How much was it?

610
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:36,039
Who cares how much?

611
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:38,480
I told you not to buy it.

612
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:39,160
Look at you...

613
00:29:39,160 --> 00:29:41,000
You're always wasting money like this.

614
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:41,799
You... this, this, this...

615
00:29:41,799 --> 00:29:42,240
No, no.

616
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:43,240
What do I earn money for?

617
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,880
Isn't it to buy you things?

618
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:46,359
When I go to work later...

619
00:29:46,359 --> 00:29:48,039
I'll have to take it off.

620
00:29:48,039 --> 00:29:49,039
What if I lose it?

621
00:29:49,039 --> 00:29:50,240
What would we do then?

622
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:51,599
See, see? You... you're such a...

623
00:29:51,599 --> 00:29:53,000
You just held it together for a little bit...

624
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:55,240
You're still destined for manual labor, I'm telling you.

625
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:57,240
This... this must be really expensive, right?

626
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:59,880
Annoying. Wasting money.

627
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:02,160
Do you like it?

628
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:05,079
This... you...

629
00:30:05,279 --> 00:30:06,599
You... you...

630
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:10,200
Just say you like it, for goodness' sake.

631
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:11,119
No, I...

632
00:30:11,599 --> 00:30:13,160
I'll even wear it to sleep.

633
00:30:13,160 --> 00:30:15,960
Just don't lose it or anything later.

634
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:18,559
As long as you like it.

635
00:30:19,200 --> 00:30:20,200
Go to sleep.

636
00:30:21,759 --> 00:30:23,599
Put the pillow down for me.

637
00:30:23,599 --> 00:30:25,599
Who do you think you're ordering around?

638
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:27,759
Fine, fine, fine. I'll do it myself.

639
00:30:27,759 --> 00:30:29,319
Myself, myself, myself.

640
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:32,000
Such a hard life.

641
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,000
Hurry up.

642
00:30:39,599 --> 00:30:40,759
Faster.

643
00:30:40,759 --> 00:30:42,200
No, are you going to sleep with it on?

644
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:43,079
Let's take it off.

645
00:30:43,079 --> 00:30:44,720
You... why do you talk so much?

646
00:30:44,720 --> 00:30:46,400
You get in bed first. Turn off the light.

647
00:30:48,839 --> 00:30:50,480
Get in.

648
00:30:55,799 --> 00:30:57,200
Weiguo: five hundred thousand.

649
00:30:57,440 --> 00:31:00,039
Manager Qiu's deposit commission: one hundred thousand.

650
00:31:02,519 --> 00:31:04,640
Weiguo buying my shares: five hundred thousand.

651
00:31:05,519 --> 00:31:07,279
Manager Qiu's deposit commission: one hundred thousand.

652
00:31:07,279 --> 00:31:09,119
I still have less than one hundred ninety thousand myself.

653
00:31:11,039 --> 00:31:13,160
It'll work. It'll work.

654
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:15,920
It'll work.

655
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:24,799
It'll work.

656
00:32:04,559 --> 00:32:05,519
Alright then.

657
00:32:06,519 --> 00:32:07,200
Great.

658
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:08,279
From now on...

659
00:32:08,279 --> 00:32:10,480
Dong Qian is our official partner.

660
00:32:10,799 --> 00:32:12,680
We're a family again.

661
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:14,400
Then let's have a pleasant cooperation from now on.

662
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:15,160
Pleasant cooperation.

663
00:32:15,160 --> 00:32:15,759
Pleasant.

664
00:32:16,039 --> 00:32:18,960
Good. From now on, it's a partnership.

665
00:32:24,799 --> 00:32:26,519
Big Bro, I've got something else to do.

666
00:32:26,519 --> 00:32:27,559
So I'll head off first.

667
00:32:28,039 --> 00:32:29,000
Leaving?

668
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:31,279
Uh, see him out.

669
00:32:31,440 --> 00:32:32,559
I'm off, Weiguo.

670
00:32:32,759 --> 00:32:33,759
See him out.

671
00:32:33,759 --> 00:32:34,279
No need, Big Bro.

672
00:32:34,279 --> 00:32:35,160
I'll walk you out.

673
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:36,200
Really, it's fine.

674
00:32:41,759 --> 00:32:43,200
Why are you two acting so weird?

675
00:32:45,799 --> 00:32:47,000
What nonsense are you talking?

676
00:32:48,759 --> 00:32:50,680
I've got things to do too, I'm off.

677
00:32:59,680 --> 00:33:01,960
Sorry for asking you out on such short notice.

678
00:33:02,240 --> 00:33:04,440
I just suddenly became very interested in some things.

679
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:06,039
I think you can give me the answers.

680
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:09,680
The reason you stirred up all that trouble...

681
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:11,799
...was to take Lianbao's shares...

682
00:33:11,799 --> 00:33:13,440
...in Hive Tech, right?

683
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:16,400
Or rather...

684
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:18,400
...the reason you were willing to invest in Pengle Xuan before...

685
00:33:18,519 --> 00:33:19,599
...was for this.

686
00:33:20,759 --> 00:33:21,319
Sorry.

687
00:33:21,319 --> 00:33:22,400
That's a trade secret.

688
00:33:22,519 --> 00:33:23,599
I can't tell you.

689
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:27,279
I don't know how important this Hive Tech...

690
00:33:27,279 --> 00:33:29,039
...really is to you.

691
00:33:29,279 --> 00:33:30,799
But I'll figure it out soon.

692
00:33:31,119 --> 00:33:32,519
I hope you don't try any tricks.

693
00:33:32,759 --> 00:33:35,519
Martin, you should think first...

694
00:33:35,519 --> 00:33:36,799
...about how to live a little longer.

695
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:39,599
You worry about yourself first.

696
00:33:56,799 --> 00:33:57,559
Lao Zhang.

697
00:33:58,119 --> 00:34:00,160
I want to make a deal with you.

698
00:34:01,039 --> 00:34:03,119
I can give up all my equity in Rice.

699
00:34:03,519 --> 00:34:05,039
But you have to do me one last favor.

700
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:08,360
Kevin has invested in many new agricultural companies...

701
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:10,760
...in Southeast Asia and China these past two years.

702
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:12,639
And he's been in frequent contact...

703
00:34:12,639 --> 00:34:14,119
...with various countries' agriculture ministries.

704
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:16,599
Hive is a company that makes entertainment-focused...

705
00:34:16,599 --> 00:34:18,400
...wearable products.

706
00:34:18,599 --> 00:34:20,320
I don't see any connection to agriculture.

707
00:34:20,679 --> 00:34:23,000
Maybe you're overthinking it.

708
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:26,079
Alright, I'll think about it some more.

709
00:35:28,519 --> 00:35:29,599
Naive.

710
00:35:34,159 --> 00:35:35,199
You...

711
00:35:35,559 --> 00:35:37,400
...don't reply to messages or answer calls.

712
00:35:37,719 --> 00:35:39,119
I thought you were rejecting me again.

713
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,599
I was just on a call.

714
00:35:45,239 --> 00:35:47,119
You finally took the initiative to ask me out.

715
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:52,119
Because I understood a saying.

716
00:35:53,039 --> 00:35:55,519
"Only the fish knows if the water is warm or cold."

717
00:35:56,559 --> 00:35:59,079
A lot of things in life are probably like that.

718
00:36:00,480 --> 00:36:02,199
He didn't force me...

719
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:04,280
...to not drink this coffee.

720
00:36:04,719 --> 00:36:07,280
Later, he didn't insist on living...

721
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:08,800
...his carefree life either.

722
00:36:08,880 --> 00:36:10,480
When two people are together...

723
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,239
...you can't just think about yourself.

724
00:36:12,239 --> 00:36:14,760
You have to consider the other person too.

725
00:36:15,039 --> 00:36:15,800
Right?

726
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:19,360
So you were convinced by her just like that?

727
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:22,840
I wouldn't say I was convinced by her.

728
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:24,840
I figured it out myself.

729
00:36:24,960 --> 00:36:26,360
Some of my own problems.

730
00:36:26,760 --> 00:36:27,480
What problems?

731
00:36:30,079 --> 00:36:31,840
I always say you're self-righteous...

732
00:36:32,159 --> 00:36:35,000
...but actually, the self-righteous one is me.

733
00:36:35,159 --> 00:36:36,960
I thought the onlooker sees most of the game.

734
00:36:38,320 --> 00:36:40,000
But actually, with many things...

735
00:36:40,480 --> 00:36:42,159
...only when you're in the situation yourself...

736
00:36:42,480 --> 00:36:44,400
...do you know what the hardship is like.

737
00:36:46,079 --> 00:36:46,719
Of course...

738
00:36:46,719 --> 00:36:48,599
...it's quite easy to give advice to others.

739
00:36:49,199 --> 00:36:50,840
But actually, I shouldn't have done that.

740
00:36:52,360 --> 00:36:53,920
Of course, I definitely hope...

741
00:36:53,920 --> 00:36:55,320
...you can have the surgery as soon as possible.

742
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:57,360
It's just that from now on...

743
00:36:58,599 --> 00:36:59,719
...I won't...

744
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:02,920
...force my ideas onto you.

745
00:37:11,119 --> 00:37:12,599
About that photography exhibition...

746
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:15,360
...can you help me contact some venues?

747
00:37:15,599 --> 00:37:17,119
If the exhibition makes a profit...

748
00:37:17,119 --> 00:37:18,400
...I can give you a cut.

749
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:21,400
What about that blond friend of yours?

750
00:37:21,920 --> 00:37:22,800
Xiaoqi?

751
00:37:23,039 --> 00:37:24,280
I don't know his name.

752
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:28,400
He went home to deal with other things.

753
00:37:32,239 --> 00:37:32,920
Alright?

754
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:34,280
Alright.

755
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:36,760
After I finish handling things at the shop...

756
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:37,719
...I'll help you.

757
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:39,599
It's settled then.

758
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:41,199
Deal.

759
00:37:41,599 --> 00:37:42,280
I will.

760
00:37:43,360 --> 00:37:44,280
No going back on your word.

761
00:37:48,159 --> 00:37:48,840
Okay.

762
00:38:20,360 --> 00:38:22,360
The cold cucumber salad for table three is almost ready, right?

763
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:23,840
Almost ready, almost ready.

764
00:38:31,559 --> 00:38:32,920
You scared me! What are you doing?

765
00:38:32,920 --> 00:38:33,760
I'm busy!

766
00:38:34,239 --> 00:38:36,320
I saw this from way over there...

767
00:38:36,519 --> 00:38:38,239
...it's so shiny!

768
00:38:38,239 --> 00:38:39,559
Really dazzling.

769
00:38:39,559 --> 00:38:42,400
I'm telling you, my hand feels heavy wearing this.

770
00:38:43,039 --> 00:38:44,719
You're just secretly pleased with yourself.

771
00:38:44,719 --> 00:38:45,960
I'm always afraid it'll fall into a dish.

772
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:47,960
Don't let a customer chew on it.

773
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:50,239
Food's coming up!

774
00:38:51,960 --> 00:38:52,719
Cucumber salad.

775
00:38:53,719 --> 00:38:54,400
Taking the cucumber salad over.

776
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:55,760
Thanks for the hard work, really.

777
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:00,440
What did I come here for?

778
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:01,480
All the dishes are here.

779
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:02,719
Big Bro.

780
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:04,719
If the flavor isn't to your liking, just let me know.

781
00:39:04,719 --> 00:39:05,679
Sis-in-law, everything's okay now?

782
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:08,239
When was there ever a problem?

783
00:39:08,800 --> 00:39:10,199
Right, your...

784
00:39:10,199 --> 00:39:12,159
...how's that Harvard thing going?

785
00:39:12,239 --> 00:39:13,559
Here we go again.

786
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:16,239
No, I'm applying for the visa right now.

787
00:39:16,239 --> 00:39:17,159
What are you planning?

788
00:39:17,239 --> 00:39:18,679
I'll go with you!

789
00:39:18,679 --> 00:39:20,239
No, it's such a major surgery...

790
00:39:20,239 --> 00:39:21,719
...and it's a new technology too.

791
00:39:21,719 --> 00:39:23,239
I won't feel at ease if I don't go.

792
00:39:23,239 --> 00:39:24,199
No need, Big Bro.

793
00:39:24,199 --> 00:39:25,440
I'm a grown adult, it's not necessary.

794
00:39:25,719 --> 00:39:27,199
What do you mean 'not necessary'?

795
00:39:27,199 --> 00:39:28,039
Chef!

796
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:29,400
This plate...

797
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:30,679
Right, right, right.

798
00:39:30,679 --> 00:39:31,119
Go attend to your work.

799
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:32,159
Listen to me, I'm telling you...

800
00:39:32,159 --> 00:39:33,159
...we're settling it like this.

801
00:39:33,159 --> 00:39:33,880
You hurry back and get some rest.

802
00:39:33,880 --> 00:39:34,760
We'll talk later, we'll talk.

803
00:39:34,760 --> 00:39:36,400
Don't you 'we'll talk later' me!

804
00:39:37,320 --> 00:39:38,360
Coming, coming!

805
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:41,719
Plate!

806
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:43,639
Sis-in-law.

807
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:45,599
You and Big Bro are okay now?

808
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:46,440
That's good, really good.

809
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:48,039
You hurry, hurry back and rest.

810
00:39:48,039 --> 00:39:49,199
You take care and rest.

811
00:39:49,199 --> 00:39:50,719
You're positively glowing.

812
00:39:51,920 --> 00:39:52,639
I'm off.

813
00:39:52,679 --> 00:39:53,880
Get some good rest.

814
00:40:08,239 --> 00:40:09,920
Uncle, I need to talk to you.

815
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:13,119
Close the door.

816
00:40:13,199 --> 00:40:13,800
Okay.

817
00:40:21,159 --> 00:40:22,639
Go ahead, what is it?

818
00:40:23,679 --> 00:40:25,719
Never mind, you don't have to say it. I know.

819
00:40:26,360 --> 00:40:27,679
You have a crush on someone, right?

820
00:40:28,199 --> 00:40:29,559
Is it a classmate or an online friend?

821
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:32,119
Neither.

822
00:40:33,880 --> 00:40:36,360
She's just a really pretty girl.

823
00:40:37,679 --> 00:40:40,119
Uncle, when you like someone...

824
00:40:40,639 --> 00:40:42,079
...should you tell her?

825
00:40:43,320 --> 00:40:45,039
That depends.

826
00:40:45,320 --> 00:40:46,440
But first, you need to be sure...

827
00:40:46,440 --> 00:40:47,559
...if she likes you back.

828
00:40:49,599 --> 00:40:51,440
I really can't be sure about that.

829
00:40:53,639 --> 00:40:54,679
Then you should just tell her.

830
00:40:55,119 --> 00:40:56,519
It's always better to say it than not.

831
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:58,159
So you won't regret it later.

832
00:40:58,360 --> 00:40:59,280
However...

833
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:00,760
You need to be mentally prepared.

